    <p class="v3-story-label">Our Story</p>
    <div class="v3-story-body" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
      <p>Green Horizon began with a walk. An unplanned detour off the main road south of Balchik, through a belt of old oak and hornbeam, that ended abruptly at a cliff edge. Below: the Black Sea. Above: open sky. Between: nothing but wind and a long way down.</p>
      <p>The family that owns this land has farmed it, planted it, and argued over it for four generations. The decision to build a hotel here was not taken lightly. It took eighteen months of family meetings, three architects, and one very stubborn structural engineer.</p>
      <p>He was right. The cliff has been here since the Eocene epoch. The hotel we are building acknowledges that. It does not compete with the landscape — it observes it. Every room faces the sea. Every terrace is positioned for the morning light.</p>
      <p>We are not in the hospitality industry. We are a family who found a place so improbable, so far from what the travel brochures call the Bulgarian coast, that we felt obliged to share it — carefully, and only with people who will understand what it is.</p>
    </div>
